==Abilities==
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Deadpool & Wolverine. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
*'''Master Combatant''': [[File:B-15 vs Minuteman-.png|thumb|250px|B-15 fights against the [[Minutemen]]]] B-15 was one of the most valuable hunters in the [[Time Variance Authority]] and was skilled in multiple forms of combat, holding her own against the equally-skilled [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] with the aid of her [[Time Stick]] and even briefly countering the latter's superhuman strength, though he soon overpowered her and used a [[Time Twister]] to teleport her away. Betraying the TVA, she fought guards who were specifically trained to protect the [[Time-Keepers]]. She fought another skilled hunter in [[Hunter X-05|Brad Wolfe]] to steal his [[TemPad]].
*'''Staff Mastery''': B-15 used her [[Time Stick]] many times and was a great fighter because of it.
*'''Expert Tactician''': Upon the [[Release of the Multiverse]], B-15 was promoted to be one of the high-ranking officials of the [[Time Variance Authority]] and thus made many strategic decisions. She was part of the main forces that took [[Mr. Paradox]] and his team down. She also felt for [[Wolverine]]'s situation and allowed him to stay on [[Earth-10005]].

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''[[Time Stick]]''': B-15 uses her Time Stick to beat and slow people down, as well as to "reset" them. She used the Time Stick to slow down [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and put the TVA collar when on him on their first encounter. She later used it to ambush Loki when he attempted to run from the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA headquarters]]. She almost accidentally reset [[Casey]] with the Time Stick when swiping at Loki.
*'''[[Sylvie Laufeydottir's Sword]]''': B-15 snatched the sword out of [[Ravonna Renslayer]]'s office and gave it to [[Sylvie Laufeydottir]] in the [[Time-Keepers]] chamber.

===Other Equipment===
*'''Uniform''': B-15 wore a Hunter's uniform and helmet. However, after B-15 realized the truth about her being a Variant, she removed her helmet.
*'''[[Tesseract]]''': B-15 carried the Tesseract after arresting [[Loki/New York Time Heist|Loki]] and taking him to the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA]], where she passed it to [[Casey]] to be archived.
*'''[[Time Twister]]''': B-15 used this device to control Loki in the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA]], returning him to his initial position when he tried to escape from her.
*'''[[TemPad]]''': B-15 used this device several times to identify Variants like Loki, and to call in for reinforcements.
**'''[[Timedoor]]''': B-15 used Timedoors to get from one location to the next on missions. She opened a Timedoor to go to a location outside of the TVA so that Laufeydottir could help her remember her past life.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Time Variance Authority Office]]''': B-15 was an agent of the [[Time Variance Authority]] and operated out of its headquarters. She was imprisoned in the headquarters upon her discovery that she was a variant with a life on the timeline, and was later freed and given the chance to watch the Multiverse open and fight for the TVA to change.

